nodes.title: DB Issues
nodes.body:
- [ ] File: webUrl broken:
URLs for older files refer to an URL for the current branch.
Example: `yarn.lock`, which does not exist in the project anymore, refers to `.../blob/feature/102/...` if DB was constructed on branch `feature/102`.
--> The webUrl leads to a 404 page.
- [x] use the (currently empty) commits-stakeholders connection instead of the `signature` attribute in commits
- [x] use the (currently empty) issues-commits connection instead of the `mentions` attribute in issues
- [x] use the issues-stakeholders connection instead of the `author`/`assignee`/`assignees` attributes in issues
- [x] use the commits-commits connection instead of the `parents`/`history` attributes in commits
- [ ] add branches-commits connection instead of using the `branch` attribute in commits
- [x] add commits-builds connection instead of using the `sha`/`ref` attributes in builds
- [ ] add builds-stakeholders connections instead of using the `user`/`userFullName` attributes in builds
- [x] rename collections according to edge direction (for example: `stakeholders-commits` instead of `commits-stakeholders` since in this collection, `_from` points to stakeholders and `_to` points to commits)

Visualizations don't load in Dashboard when adding a new one
nodes.body: When adding a new visualization to the dashboard it doesn't load and waits for an update either from the backend or by refreshing the page. This should be fixed so that when it gets added it immediately loads the current state.

nodes.title: Update CI Indexer to be more efficient and use fewer API Requests
nodes.body: Currently, the CI Indexer uses a lot of API Requests. This could be reduced significantly by changing all the GitLab requests to one single GraphQL Requests and reducing the Github request by not requesting each pipeline individually.
